-- Spain's FCC Koplowitz sells rights to Mexico's Slim for 150 mln euros
-- By Paul Day
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 02:42AM EST
-- None



MADRID, Dec 4 (Reuters) - Mexican billionaire Carlos Slim has acquired the subscription rights in Spanish builder FCC <FCC.MC> from top shareholder Esther Koplowitz for 150 million euros ($184.50 million), FCC said on Thursday.

Control Empresarial de Capitales, owned by Slim, bought 63.7 million preferential subscription rights from Koplowitz investor vehicles B-1998 and Azate for 2.3553 euros per right, FCC said.